   "source": [
    "# 25. What is Data Leakage? List some ways using which you can overcome this problem."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9ae441e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "✅ What is Data Leakage?\n",
    "\n",
    "Data leakage happens when your model gets access to information it shouldn’t have at training time, especially data that would not be available in real-world predictions.\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Result:\n",
    "\n",
    "Model shows very high accuracy during training/testing\n",
    "But performs poorly in production ❌\n",
    "🎯 Simple Example\n",
    "Predicting house prices\n",
    "You include a feature like “final selling price after negotiation”\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 That’s future information → leakage\n",
    "\n",
    "⚠️ Types of Data Leakage\n",
    "🔹 1. Target Leakage\n",
    "Features directly or indirectly contain target info\n",
    "Example: medical diagnosis using post-treatment results\n",
    "🔹 2. Train-Test Contamination\n",
    "Test data influences training process\n",
    "Example: scaling entire dataset before splitting\n",
    "🔹 3. Time Leakage\n",
    "Future data used to predict past\n",
    "Common in time-series problems\n",
    "🚀 How to Prevent Data Leakage?\n",
    "✅ 1. Proper Train-Test Split (First step)\n",
    "Always split data before preprocessing\n",
    "✅ 2. Use Pipelines\n",
    "Apply transformations separately on train/test\n",
    "Tools like Scikit-learn pipelines help avoid leakage\n",
    "✅ 3. Feature Selection Carefully\n",
    "Remove features that:\n",
    "Contain future info\n",
    "Are derived from target\n",
    "✅ 4. Time-Based Splitting (for time-series)\n",
    "Train on past → test on future\n",
    "Never random shuffle\n",
    "✅ 5. Cross-Validation Properly\n",
    "Ensure no data overlap between folds\n",
    "✅ 6. Avoid Data Snooping\n",
    "Don’t repeatedly tune model on test set\n",
    "✅ 7. Separate Preprocessing\n",
    "Fit scaler/encoder only on training data\n",
    "🎯 Interview-Ready Answer (Short)**\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Data leakage occurs when information from outside the training dataset, especially future or target-related data, is used to train the model, leading to overly optimistic performance. It can be prevented by proper train-test splitting, using pipelines, careful feature selection, time-based validation, and ensuring preprocessing is done only on training data.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 Pro Tip\n",
    "\n",
    "Say this in interview 👇\n",
    "👉 “If your model accuracy is too good to be true, suspect data leakage.”"
   ]
  },
